Introduction
Hurricane Beryl, a Category 5 hurricane, made history by becoming the first hurricane of its strength to strike the Caribbean in June. This project aims to provide a comprehensive analysis of Beryl's trajectory, intensity, and the resulting damage. By leveraging data from the National Hurricane Center (NHC) and other meteorological sources, we aim to present our findings through various visualizations to better understand the hurricane's impact.

Data Sources
The data used in this project is sourced from:

National Hurricane Center (NHC)
Other meteorological sources
